Following Mondayâ€™s incident of a man jumping off the Ambedkar Nagar police station terrace, fresh instructions for questioning procedure have been issued. According to sources, the station house officer was not in the loop in the Ambedkar Nagar case.Sources said all the police stations of the South Eastern range have now been told that questioning of suspects shall be done on the ground floor and nobody can be taken to the higher floors. Further, it is learnt that it has been made mandatory for staff to intimate their respective station house officers before carrying out questioning.